Peter is a tech explorer with a background in electrical engineering and information technology. He earned a PhD in Information System, mostly reading on philosophy of knowledge, which is more fun than it sounds.

For over 15 years, he has worked as a university lecturer, teaching a variety of information technology subjects. He has also worked as an independent developer and consultant, building web and smartphone applications for small/medium sized enterprises.

In the last couple of years, Peter has returned to his childhood passion, tinkering with electronics. He has created 5 courses on the topics of Arduino and Raspberry Pi development and his latest, printed circuit board design. He published his courses on Udemy.
